import React from "react";

const Personal = (props) => {
    const personalInfo = props.personalInfo
    const personalName = props.personalName
    const personalEmail = props.personalEmail
    const personalPhone = props.personalPhone
    const personalCity = props.personalCity
    const personalBirthDate = props.personalBirthDate
    const personalCar = props.personalCar

    return <>
    <form className="personal">
        <label htmlFor="nameInput" > Enter full name </label>
        <input
        onChange={personalName}
        value={personalInfo.name}
        type='text'
        id="nameInput"
        />

        <label htmlFor="emailInput" > Enter your email </label>
        <input
        onChange={personalEmail}
        value={personalInfo.email}
        type='text'
        id="emailInput"
        />

        <label htmlFor="phoneInput" > Enter your phone number </label>
        <input
        onChange={personalPhone}
        value={personalInfo.phone}
        type='text'
        id="phoneInput"
        />



    <label htmlFor="birthDateInput" > Enter your birth date</label>
        <input
        onChange={personalBirthDate}
        value={personalInfo.birthDate}
        type='text'
        id="birthDateInput"
        />

    <label htmlFor="carInput" > Do you have a license </label>
        <input
        onChange={personalCar}
        value={personalInfo.car}
        type='text'
        id="carInput"
        />
        <button>save Changes</button>
    </form>
    </>
}

export default Personal;
